import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy - Leszek Pomianowski">
  <div class="page">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> October 17, 2025</p>
    
    <h2>Introduction</h2>
    <p>
      This Privacy Policy describes how Leszek Pomianowski ("we," "our," or "us") collects, 
      uses, and protects your information when you use our applications, websites, and services, 
      including but not limited to Radiograph, WPF UI, and related software products.
    </p>
    
    <p>
      We are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring transparency about our data practices. 
      This policy applies to all our applications available through the Microsoft Store, 
      our websites, and any related services.
    </p>
    
    <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
    
    <h3>Information You Provide</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Contact Information:</strong> Email addresses when you contact us for support or inquiries</li>
      <li><strong>Feedback and Communications:</strong> Messages, bug reports, and feature requests you send to us</li>
      <li><strong>Support Requests:</strong> Technical information you provide when seeking assistance</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h3>Information Collected Automatically</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> Information about how you use our applications and services</li>
      <li><strong>Device Information:</strong> Hardware and software information necessary for application functionality</li>
      <li><strong>Performance Data:</strong> Application performance metrics and crash reports (when opted in)</li>
      <li><strong>System Information:</strong> Operating system version, hardware specifications (for monitoring applications like Radiograph)</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h3>Information We Do NOT Collect</h3>
    <p>We want to be clear about what we do NOT collect:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Personal files or documents from your computer</li>
      <li>Browsing history or web activity</li>
      <li>Passwords or authentication credentials</li>
      <li>Financial or payment information (handled by Microsoft Store/payment processors)</li>
      <li>Location data beyond general region for localization</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
    
    <h3>Application Functionality</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Hardware Monitoring:</strong> For applications like Radiograph, we access hardware sensors to provide monitoring functionality</li>
      <li><strong>Performance Optimization:</strong> Using performance data to improve application stability and speed</li>
      <li><strong>Feature Development:</strong> Understanding usage patterns to develop relevant features</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h3>Communication and Support</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Customer Support:</strong> Responding to your inquiries and providing technical assistance</li>
      <li><strong>Product Updates:</strong> Notifying you about important updates or security issues</li>
      <li><strong>Community Engagement:</strong> Facilitating discussions about our open-source projects</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h3>Legal and Safety</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Compliance:</strong> Meeting legal obligations and platform requirements</li>
      <li><strong>Security:</strong> Protecting against fraud, abuse, and security threats</li>
      <li><strong>Platform Requirements:</strong> Complying with Microsoft Store and other platform policies</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2>Data Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
    
    <h3>We Do Not Sell Your Data</h3>
    <p>
      We do not sell, rent, or lease your personal information to third parties. 
      Your privacy is not for sale.
    </p>
    
    <h3>Limited Sharing</h3>
    <p>We may share information only in these specific circumstances:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Service Providers:</strong> With trusted partners who help us operate our services (e.g., hosting providers, analytics services)</li>
      <li><strong>Platform Requirements:</strong> With platform operators (Microsoft Store) as required for app distribution</li>
      <li><strong>Legal Requirements:</strong> When required by law or to protect rights and safety</li>
      <li><strong>Business Transfers:</strong> In the event of a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets (with advance notice)</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h3>Open Source Projects</h3>
    <p>
      For our open-source projects (WPF UI, contributions to LibreHardwareMonitor), 
      any contributions you make to public repositories are governed by the respective 
      project licenses and GitHub's terms of service.
    </p>
    
    <h2>Data Security</h2>
    
    <h3>Protection Measures</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Encryption:</strong> Data transmission is encrypted using industry-standard protocols</li>
      <li><strong>Access Controls:</strong> Limited access to personal information on a need-to-know basis</li>
      <li><strong>Regular Audits:</strong> Periodic review of our security practices and data handling</li>
      <li><strong>Secure Infrastructure:</strong> Using reputable hosting and service providers with strong security practices</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h3>Data Retention</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Support Communications:</strong> Retained for up to 3 years for support purposes</li>
      <li><strong>Usage Analytics:</strong> Aggregated and anonymized data may be retained indefinitely</li>
      <li><strong>Account Deletion:</strong> Personal data deleted within 30 days of account deletion request</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2>Your Rights and Choices</h2>
    
    <h3>Access and Control</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Data Access:</strong> Request a copy of the personal data we have about you</li>
      <li><strong>Data Correction:</strong> Request correction of inaccurate or incomplete data</li>
      <li><strong>Data Deletion:</strong> Request deletion of your personal data (subject to legal requirements)</li>
      <li><strong>Data Portability:</strong> Request your data in a machine-readable format</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h3>Communication Preferences</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Email Communications:</strong> Opt out of non-essential communications</li>
      <li><strong>Analytics:</strong> Disable usage analytics in supported applications</li>
      <li><strong>Crash Reporting:</strong> Control whether crash reports are sent</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h3>Application-Specific Controls</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Radiograph:</strong> Control which hardware sensors are monitored</li>
      <li><strong>WPF UI Applications:</strong> Configure telemetry and feedback options</li>
      <li><strong>Microsoft Store:</strong> Use Microsoft Store privacy controls for app permissions</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
    <p>
      Our services are not directed to children under 13 years of age. We do not 
      knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you become 
      aware that a child has provided us with personal information, please contact us 
      so we can take appropriate action.
    </p>
    
    <h2>International Data Transfers</h2>
    <p>
      Your information may be processed and stored in countries other than your own. 
      We ensure appropriate safeguards are in place to protect your data in accordance 
      with applicable privacy laws and regulations.
    </p>
    
    <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we make significant changes, 
      we will notify you through our applications, website, or by email. The "Last updated" 
      date at the top of this policy indicates when it was last revised.
    </p>
    
    <p>
      We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically to stay informed 
      about how we protect your information.
    </p>
    
    <h2>Platform-Specific Information</h2>
    
    <h3>Microsoft Store Applications</h3>
    <p>
      For applications distributed through the Microsoft Store (such as Radiograph), 
      additional privacy protections and controls may be available through Windows 
      privacy settings and Microsoft Store policies.
    </p>
    
    <h3>GitHub and Open Source</h3>
    <p>
      Contributions to our open-source projects on GitHub are subject to GitHub's 
      privacy policy and terms of service. Repository activity, issues, and pull 
      requests are generally public.
    </p>
    
    <h2>Contact Information</h2>
    <p>
      If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, 
      please contact us at:
    </p>
    
    <p>
      <strong>Email:</strong> support at lepo.co (replace "at" with @)<br>
      <strong>Subject:</strong> Privacy Policy Inquiry
    </p>
    
    <p>
      For specific data requests (access, correction, deletion), please include:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Your contact information</li>
      <li>Specific applications or services you're inquiring about</li>
      <li>The nature of your request</li>
      <li>Any relevant account information</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2>Legal Basis for Processing (EU/UK Users)</h2>
    <p>
      For users in the European Union and United Kingdom, we process your personal 
      data based on the following legal grounds:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Legitimate Interest:</strong> Improving our products and providing support</li>
      <li><strong>Contract Performance:</strong> Providing services you've requested</li>
      <li><strong>Consent:</strong> When you've explicitly agreed to data processing</li>
      <li><strong>Legal Obligation:</strong> Complying with applicable laws and regulations</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2>Effective Date</h2>
    <p>
      This Privacy Policy is effective as of October 17, 2025, and applies to all 
      information collected on or after this date. Previous versions of our privacy 
      policy governed data collection prior to this date.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

